You need the `maven-jar-plugin` (see [Maven&#39;s example][1]). This plugin will create the required entries in the manifest file when the project is built.
```xml
&lt;project&gt;
  ...
  &lt;build&gt;
    &lt;plugins&gt;
      ...
      &lt;plugin&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-jar-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;2.3.2&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;configuration&gt;
          &lt;archive&gt;
            &lt;manifest&gt;
              &lt;addClasspath&gt;true&lt;/addClasspath&gt;
              &lt;mainClass&gt;fully.qualified.MainClass&lt;/mainClass&gt;
            &lt;/manifest&gt;
          &lt;/archive&gt;
        &lt;/configuration&gt;
      &lt;/plugin&gt;
      ...
    &lt;/plugins&gt;
  &lt;/build&gt;
  ...
&lt;/project&gt;
```
You need the version, otherwise, the project won&#39;t build. The `fully.qualified.MainClass` starts at the package hierarchy.

  [1]: http://maven.apache.org/shared/maven-archiver/examples/classpath.html#Make

